724742f-b.title: Manhattan: West Street - Jane Street
724742f-b.text:
(1)
American Seaman's Friend Society, 505-507 West Street at the
N.E. corner of Jane Street, opposite Pier 51, North River.
The building was erected in 1907. Its hexagonal tower is
an outstanding landmark.
May 12, 1927.
P. L. Sperr.
NO REPRODUCTIONS.
Ace, ~ 2623
(2)
The same, two years later.
March 8, 1929.
